quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  21,76,"And (remember) Nuh, when he cried (to Us) aforetime. We answered to his invocation and saved him and his family from the great distress"
  21,77,"We helped him against the people who denied Our Ayat. Verily, they were a people given to evil. So We drowned them all"
  21,78,"And (remember) Dawud and Sulayman, when they gave judgement in the case of the field in which the sheep of certain people had Nafashat; and We were witness to their judgement"
  21,79,And We made Sulayman to understand (the case); and to each of them We gave wisdom (Hukm) and knowledge. And We subjected the mountains and the birds to glorify Our praises along with Dawud. And it was We Who were the doer (of all these things)
  21,80,"And We taught him the making of metal coats of mail (for battles), to protect you in your fighting. Are you then grateful"
  21,81,"And to Sulayman (We subjected) the wind strongly raging, running by his command towards the land which We had blessed. And of everything We are the All-Knower"
  21,82,"And of the Shayatin were some who dived for him, and did other work besides that; and it was We Who guarded them"
  21,83,"And (remember) Ayyub, when he cried to his Lord: \"Verily, distress has seized me, and You are the Most Merciful of all those who show mercy"
  21,84,"So We answered his call, and We removed the distress that was on him, and We restored his family to him, and the like thereof along with them as a mercy from Ourselves and a Reminder for all those who worship Us"
  21,85,"And (remember) Isma`il, Idris and Dhul-Kifl: All were from among the patient"
  21,86,"And We admitted them to Our mercy. Verily, they were of the righteous"
  21,87,"And (remember) Dhun-Nun, when he went off in anger, and imagined that We shall not punish him! But he cried through the darknesses (Zulumat) (saying): \"There is no God but You, Glorified be You! Truly, I have been of the Zalimin wrongdoers"
  21,88,"So We answered his call, and delivered him from the distress. And thus We do deliver the believers"
  21,89,"And (remember) Zakariyya, when he cried to his Lord: \"O My Lord! Leave me not single (childless), though You are the Best of the inheritors"
  21,90,"So We answered his call, and We bestowed upon him Yahya, and cured his wife for him. Verily, they used to hasten on to do good deeds, and they used to call on Us with hope and fear, and they were Khashi`in before Us"
  21,91,"And she who guarded her chastity, We breathed into her through Our Ruh, and We made her and her son a sign for nations"
  21,92,"Truly, this, your Ummah is one, and I am your Lord, therefore worship Me"
  21,93,But they have broken up and differed in their religion among themselves. (And) they all shall return to Us